# D14c_KRAS_STRATIFIED_v1
# Pre-registration: KRAS-stratified TCGA COAD coexpression — EGFR structural position test
# Date: 2026-06-07
# Status: PRE-REGISTERED — do not parse MAF files or compute stratified coexpression before this commit

## Scientific background

D14b result: EGFR is the strongest structural DAMPER in the 100-node TCGA COAD network
(z_dr = +2.411). This is remarkable because EGFR inhibitors (cetuximab, panitumumab)
are FDA-approved for CRC — but ONLY in KRAS wild-type tumors.

KRAS mutations (codons 12/13) constitutively activate RAS signaling downstream of EGFR,
bypassing EGFR entirely. In KRAS-mutant CRC:
  - EGFR inhibition has no clinical effect (RAS drives signaling independently)
  - EGFR is structurally "bypassed" — it is no longer the gateway to the RAS/MAPK/PI3K axis

If the structural pharmacology framework is capturing pharmacologically real signal, then:
  - In KRAS-WT: EGFR should be a structural DAMPER (its removal disrupts the network;
    EGFR inhibition is clinically effective)
  - In KRAS-MT: EGFR should be near-zero or an ANCHOR (its removal does not disrupt
    the KRAS-driven network; EGFR inhibition is clinically ineffective)

This is a pre-registered falsification test of the framework's pharmacological specificity.

## Data

MAF files: 458 WXS somatic mutation files (TCGA-COAD, GDC manifest 2026-06-07.203630)
  Location: downloads/D14c/ (one MAF.gz per UUID folder)
  Format: GDC aliquot_ensemble_masked MAF v1.0

RNA-Seq files: 524 augmented STAR counts (same as D14/D14b)
  Location: downloads/D14a_b/ (same 524 TSV files)

Linking: TCGA patient barcode (first 12 chars of Tumor_Sample_Barcode: TCGA-XX-XXXX)
  is the join key between MAF and RNA-Seq samples.
  RNA-Seq UUID → patient barcode: query GDC API (no authentication required)
  OR: extract from augmented STAR TSV metadata if available

## KRAS mutation definition (pre-registered)

KRAS-mutant (KRAS-MT): sample has any somatic mutation in Hugo_Symbol == "KRAS"
  with Variant_Classification NOT in ["Silent", "3'UTR", "5'UTR", "Intron", "RNA"]
  (i.e., any protein-altering KRAS mutation)

KRAS wild-type (KRAS-WT): sample has a MAF file AND has NO qualifying KRAS mutation

Samples without a MAF file: excluded from stratified analysis, included only in the
"all samples" (D14b) comparison.

## Processing protocol (pre-registered)

1. Parse all 458 MAF files → KRAS mutation status per patient barcode
2. Map RNA-Seq UUIDs → patient barcodes via GDC API
3. Assign KRAS status to each RNA-Seq sample; exclude samples without MAF
4. Build separate log2(TPM+1) expression matrices:
   - KRAS-WT group
   - KRAS-MT group
5. For each group: compute pairwise Pearson correlation for all 97 mapped proteins
6. Threshold Layer B at r >= 0.3 (same as D14b, adjusted if <50 or >500 edges)
7. Run delta_r + 500-rewiring null for each group independently
8. Compare z_dr(EGFR) between groups

## Hypotheses

### H1: EGFR z_dr > 1.5 in KRAS-WT (structural DAMPER in EGFR-sensitive context)
  D14b all-sample result: z_dr(EGFR) = +2.411
  Prediction: z_dr(EGFR) > 1.5 in KRAS-WT samples specifically

  H1 CONFIRMED if: z_dr(EGFR) > 1.5 in KRAS-WT
  H1 DENIED if: z_dr(EGFR) <= 1.5 in KRAS-WT

### H2: EGFR z_dr < 1.0 in KRAS-MT (EGFR structurally bypassed)
  Prediction: |z_dr(EGFR)| < 1.0 OR z_dr(EGFR) negative in KRAS-MT samples

  H2 CONFIRMED if: z_dr(EGFR) < 1.0 in KRAS-MT (not a structural DAMPER)
  H2 DENIED if: z_dr(EGFR) >= 1.0 in KRAS-MT (EGFR is DAMPER regardless of KRAS)

  If both H1 and H2 confirmed: the framework correctly identifies EGFR as context-specific
  DAMPER — it captures the KRAS bypass mechanism at the structural level.

### H3: MDM2 DAMPER status maintained in both KRAS-WT and KRAS-MT
  D14b result: z_dr(MDM2) = +1.267 (all samples)
  MDM2's oncogenic DAMPER role is not KRAS-dependent — MDM2 amplification/overexpression
  occurs in CRC independently of KRAS mutation status.
  Prediction: z_dr(MDM2) > 1.0 in BOTH KRAS-WT and KRAS-MT subgroups.

  H3 CONFIRMED if: z_dr(MDM2) > 1.0 in both groups
  H3 DENIED if: z_dr(MDM2) < 1.0 in either group

### H4: MAP2K1 remains near-zero in both subgroups (boundary condition holds)
  D14b result: z_dr(MAP2K1) = -0.187 (all samples)
  Prediction: |z_dr(MAP2K1)| < 1.0 in both KRAS-WT and KRAS-MT

  H4 CONFIRMED if: |z_dr(MAP2K1)| < 1.0 in both groups
  H4 DENIED if: z_dr(MAP2K1) > 1.0 in either group (MAP2K1 DAMPER in a subtype)

  H4 denial would be interesting: KRAS status might rescue MAP2K1 structural signal
  (e.g., in KRAS-WT, MEK1 may be a more prominent pathway node than in KRAS-MT
  where KRAS drives ERK/MEK independently)

## Decision table

| H1 | H2 | Interpretation |
|----|----|----------------|
| CONF | CONF | Framework captures KRAS bypass; EGFR structural position is clinically predictive |
| CONF | DENIED | EGFR is DAMPER in both subtypes; structural signal does not track clinical selectivity |
| DENIED | CONF | EGFR not structural DAMPER even in KRAS-WT; D14b all-sample result was subtype-averaged artifact |
| DENIED | DENIED | EGFR structural position is insensitive to KRAS status |

## Sample size expectation (pre-registered)

TCGA COAD KRAS mutation frequency: ~40-45% KRAS-MT
Expected KRAS-MT RNA-Seq samples with matched MAF: ~120-160
Expected KRAS-WT RNA-Seq samples with matched MAF: ~160-220
Total stratifiable: ~300-380 of 524 RNA-Seq samples

Minimum n requirement: >= 50 samples per group for stable correlation estimates.
If either group has < 50 samples, report but flag as underpowered.

## Pre-registration caveats

1. GDC API may be needed to link RNA-Seq UUIDs to patient barcodes; if API unavailable,
   will attempt to extract barcode from augmented STAR counts file metadata
2. Some RNA-Seq samples may not have matched WXS (no MAF file) — excluded from
   stratified analysis but the n_excluded will be reported
3. KRAS codon specificity: not pre-registering codon-level analysis (G12/G13/Q61);
   any protein-altering KRAS mutation = KRAS-MT. Codon analysis is post-hoc.
4. Null model: 500 rewirings per group (same as all prior experiments)
5. Threshold adjustment applies independently per group

